Below is a clean, professional step-by-step guide for implementing GitHub Actions CI/CD with a self-hosted runner, Docker Hub, Trivy scan, and GitOps manifest update.

---

 GitHub Actions Implementation Guide

 1. Objective

This guide explains how to implement a GitHub Actions CI/CD pipeline for the repository:


nirajj-pal/GitHub-Actions


The pipeline will perform the following tasks:

1. Trigger on code changes in the main branch.
2. Build a Docker image.
3. Scan the Docker image using Trivy.
4. Push the Docker image to Docker Hub.
5. Update the Kubernetes manifest repository with the latest image tag.
6. Push the updated manifest changes to the GitOps repository.

---

 2. Repository Details

 Application Repository


nirajj-pal/GitHub-Actions


This repository contains the application source code and GitHub Actions workflow.

 Manifest Repository


nirajj-pal/sample-node-app-manifests


This repository contains the Kubernetes manifest files that will be updated by the pipeline.

Manifest path:


manifest-repo/kubernetes-manifest-main/cmsapi/dev


