 3. Configure Self-Hosted Runner

 Step 1: Open GitHub Runner Settings

Go to the application repository:


nirajj-pal/GitHub-Actions


Then open:


Settings > Actions > Runners > New self-hosted runner


Select:


Linux > x64


GitHub will display the runner registration commands.

---

 Step 2: Go to the Runner Directory

On the runner server, switch to the runner directory:

bash
cd /home/githubrunner/actions-runner


---

 Step 3: Register the Runner

Run the following command to configure the runner.

Replace `<RUNNER_TOKEN>` with the token shown on the GitHub runner setup page.

bash
sudo -u githubrunner ./config.sh \
  --url https://github.com/nirajj-pal/GitHub-Actions \
  --token <RUNNER_TOKEN> \
  --name worker-1-github-actions \
  --labels docker-build,node-app \
  --work _work \
  --unattended


 Explanation

| Option         | Description                                           |
| -------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| `--url`        | GitHub repository where the runner will be registered |
| `--token`      | Runner registration token from GitHub                 |
| `--name`       | Name of the self-hosted runner                        |
| `--labels`     | Labels used by the workflow to select this runner     |
| `--work`       | Working directory used by the runner                  |
| `--unattended` | Runs the configuration without interactive prompts    |

---

 Step 4: Install and Start the Runner Service

After registration, install the runner as a system service:

bash
sudo ./svc.sh install githubrunner


Start the runner service:

bash
sudo ./svc.sh start


Check the runner service status:

bash
sudo ./svc.sh status


You can also verify the runner from GitHub:


Repository > Settings > Actions > Runners


The runner should show as Idle or Online.

---

 4. Remove an Old Runner Configuration

Use this section only if the runner was previously registered with another repository and needs to be removed.

---

 Step 1: Stop the Existing Runner Service

First, check the runner service name:

bash
systemctl list-units "actions.runner.*"


Then stop the existing service.

Example:

bash
sudo systemctl stop actions.runner.nirajj-pal-sample-node-app.worker-1.service


Disable the service:

bash
sudo systemctl disable actions.runner.nirajj-pal-sample-node-app.worker-1.service


Check the status:

bash
sudo systemctl status actions.runner.nirajj-pal-sample-node-app.worker-1.service


---

 Step 2: Remove Runner from GitHub UI

Go to the old repository where the runner was registered:


Settings > Actions > Runners


Select the runner and click:


Remove


GitHub will provide a runner removal token.

---

 Step 3: Uninstall the Runner Service

Go to the runner directory:

bash
cd /home/githubrunner/actions-runner


Uninstall the runner service:

bash
sudo ./svc.sh uninstall


---

 Step 4: Remove Runner Configuration

Replace `<OLD_RUNNER_REMOVE_TOKEN>` with the token shown in GitHub while removing the runner.

bash
sudo -u githubrunner ./config.sh remove --token <OLD_RUNNER_REMOVE_TOKEN>


After this, the runner can be registered again with the correct repository.

