 5. Create GitOps Personal Access Token

A GitHub Personal Access Token is required so that the GitHub Actions workflow can push changes to the manifest repository.

---

 Step 1: Open GitHub Token Settings

Go to GitHub:


Profile icon > Settings > Developer settings > Personal access tokens > Fine-grained tokens > Generate new token


---

 Step 2: Create the Token

Use the following values:

| Field               | Value                       |
| ------------------- | --------------------------- |
| Token name          | `GITOPS_PAT`                |
| Resource owner      | `nirajj-pal`                |
| Repository access   | Only select repositories    |
| Selected repository | `sample-node-app-manifests` |

---

 Step 3: Set Repository Permissions

Set the following permissions:

| Permission | Access         |
| ---------- | -------------- |
| Contents   | Read and write |
| Metadata   | Read           |

Then click:


Generate token


Copy the generated token and keep it safe.

---

 6. Add Repository Secrets

Go to the workflow repository:


nirajj-pal/GitHub-Actions


Open:


Settings > Secrets and variables > Actions > New repository secret


Add the following secrets:

| Secret Name          | Value                                               |
| -------------------- | --------------------------------------------------- |
| `DOCKERHUB_USERNAME` | Docker Hub username                                 |
| `DOCKERHUB_TOKEN`    | Docker Hub access token                             |
| `GITOPS_PAT`         | GitHub fine-grained PAT for the manifest repository |

Example:


DOCKERHUB_USERNAME = nirajpal
DOCKERHUB_TOKEN    = your Docker Hub access token
GITOPS_PAT         = GitHub PAT for pushing to manifest repo


