 7. Create GitHub Actions Workflow

Create the workflow file in the application repository:


.github/workflows/ci-cd.yml


Add the following pipeline:

yaml
name: CI/CD Pipeline

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - main
    paths:
      - "kubernetes-cicd-tutorial-main/"
      - ".github/workflows/ci-cd.yml"

  workflow_dispatch:

env:
  APP_DIR: kubernetes-cicd-tutorial-main

   Docker Hub image
  DOCKER_IMAGE_NAME: docker.io/nirajpal/sample-node-app

   Manifest repo
  MANIFEST_REPO: nirajj-pal/sample-node-app-manifests
  MANIFEST_BRANCH: main
  MANIFEST_PATH: manifest-repo/kubernetes-manifest-main/cmsapi/dev
  KUSTOMIZATION_FILE: kustomization.yaml

   Current image name present in kustomization.yaml
  OLD_IMAGE_NAME: harbor.lr.in/project-lr/ordermutationmsapi

jobs:
  build-and-push:
    runs-on: [self-hosted, linux, x64, docker-build]

    steps:
      - name: Checkout application repo
        uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Generate image tag
        run: |
          IMAGE_TAG=${GITHUB_SHA::8}
          echo "IMAGE_TAG=$IMAGE_TAG" >> $GITHUB_ENV
          echo "FULL_IMAGE=${DOCKER_IMAGE_NAME}:$IMAGE_TAG" >> $GITHUB_ENV

      - name: Login to Docker Hub
        run: |
          echo "${{ secrets.DOCKERHUB_TOKEN }}" | docker login docker.io \
            -u "${{ secrets.DOCKERHUB_USERNAME }}" \
            --password-stdin

      - name: Build Docker image
        run: |
          docker build -t "$FULL_IMAGE" "$APP_DIR"

      - name: Run Trivy image scan
        run: |
          mkdir -p "$HOME/.cache/trivy"

          docker run --rm \
            -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \
            -v "$HOME/.cache/trivy:/root/.cache/" \
            aquasec/trivy:0.70.0 image \
            --exit-code 0 \
            --severity HIGH,CRITICAL \
            --ignore-unfixed \
            --no-progress \
            "$FULL_IMAGE"

      - name: Push Docker image
        run: |
          docker push "$FULL_IMAGE"

      - name: Checkout manifest repo
        uses: actions/checkout@v4
        with:
          repository: ${{ env.MANIFEST_REPO }}
          ref: ${{ env.MANIFEST_BRANCH }}
          token: ${{ secrets.GITOPS_PAT }}
          path: gitops

      - name: Update kustomization.yaml image
        run: |
          cd "gitops/${MANIFEST_PATH}"

          echo "Before update:"
          cat "${KUSTOMIZATION_FILE}"

          python3 - <<EOF
          from pathlib import Path

          file = Path("${KUSTOMIZATION_FILE}")
          content = file.read_text().splitlines()

          old_image = "${OLD_IMAGE_NAME}"
          new_image = "${DOCKER_IMAGE_NAME}"
          new_tag = "${IMAGE_TAG}"

          output = []
          inside_image_block = False
          image_found = False
          new_name_written = False
          new_tag_written = False

          for line in content:
              stripped = line.strip()

              if stripped == f"- name: {old_image}":
                  inside_image_block = True
                  image_found = True
                  new_name_written = False
                  new_tag_written = False
                  output.append(line)
                  continue

              if inside_image_block:
                  if stripped.startswith("- name:"):
                      if not new_name_written:
                          output.append("    newName: " + new_image)
                      if not new_tag_written:
                          output.append("    newTag: " + new_tag)
                      inside_image_block = False

                  elif stripped.startswith("newName:"):
                      indent = line[:len(line) - len(line.lstrip())]
                      output.append(f"{indent}newName: {new_image}")
                      new_name_written = True
                      continue

                  elif stripped.startswith("newTag:"):
                      indent = line[:len(line) - len(line.lstrip())]
                      output.append(f"{indent}newTag: {new_tag}")
                      new_tag_written = True
                      continue

              output.append(line)

          if inside_image_block:
              if not new_name_written:
                  output.append("    newName: " + new_image)
              if not new_tag_written:
                  output.append("    newTag: " + new_tag)

          if not image_found:
              raise SystemExit(f"Image name not found in kustomization.yaml: {old_image}")

          file.write_text("\\n".join(output) + "\\n")
          EOF

          echo "After update:"
          cat "${KUSTOMIZATION_FILE}"

      - name: Commit and push manifest changes
        env:
          GITOPS_PAT: ${{ secrets.GITOPS_PAT }}
        run: |
          cd gitops

          git config user.name "GitHub Actions"
          git config user.email "actions@github.com"

          git add "${MANIFEST_PATH}/${KUSTOMIZATION_FILE}"

          git commit -m "Update Docker image tag to ${IMAGE_TAG}" || echo "No changes to commit"

          git remote set-url origin "https://x-access-token:${GITOPS_PAT}@github.com/${MANIFEST_REPO}.git"

          git push origin "${MANIFEST_BRANCH}"


---

 8. Pipeline Explanation

 Trigger Section

yaml
on:
  push:
    branches:
      - main


The pipeline runs when code is pushed to the `main` branch.

yaml
paths:
  - "kubernetes-cicd-tutorial-main/"
  - ".github/workflows/ci-cd.yml"


The pipeline only runs when files inside the application directory or workflow file are changed.

yaml
workflow_dispatch:


This allows the pipeline to be triggered manually from the GitHub Actions UI.

---

 Runner Section

yaml
runs-on: [self-hosted, linux, x64, docker-build]


This tells GitHub Actions to run the pipeline on a self-hosted runner with the label:


docker-build


Make sure the runner is registered with the same label.

---

 Docker Build and Push

The pipeline generates an image tag using the short commit SHA:

bash
IMAGE_TAG=${GITHUB_SHA::8}


Example image:


docker.io/nirajpal/sample-node-app:79d61e0


Then it builds and pushes the image to Docker Hub.

---

 Trivy Image Scan

The Trivy scan checks the Docker image for vulnerabilities:

yaml
--severity HIGH,CRITICAL


This scans for high and critical vulnerabilities.

yaml
--exit-code 0


This means the pipeline will not fail even if Trivy finds high or critical vulnerabilities.

This is useful when you want visibility of vulnerabilities but do not want to block the deployment.

---

 Manifest Repository Update

The pipeline checks out the manifest repository:


nirajj-pal/sample-node-app-manifests


Then it updates the image tag in:


manifest-repo/kubernetes-manifest-main/cmsapi/dev/kustomization.yaml


Finally, it commits and pushes the updated manifest file.

